A vintage 1990s-style illustration of an old beige server tower computer being gently lowered into the earth like a burial, surrounded by a small gathering of newer, sleeker servers in black and silver standing solemnly around the grave site. The scene is set in a misty server room cemetery with rows of decommissioned hardware tombstones in the background. Soft warm tungsten lighting casts long shadows. A single Linux penguin stands nearby holding a small flower, while in the distance through a window, a sunrise hints at new beginnings. The color palette features muted browns, grays, and subtle orange tones reminiscent of faded Polaroid photographs from the early 2000s era.
